cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.IT

The paper discusses empirical universal distributions for the halting time of optimization algorithms applied to two random systems: spin glasses and deep learning. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.IT (Information Theory). However, given that the paper focuses on optimization algorithms and their applications, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also possible, as they are related to optimization and machine learning, but to a lesser extent.
